Probable usage from MSAG rules (mandatory fields prefixed with *):

<counter:create
    *name="NAME"
    *type="TEMPLID"
    inc="VALUE,default=0"
    weight="INT,default=0"         // ignored for some types
    reset="false|true,default=false"
    scope="USER|SERVICE|OPERATOR|PROVIDER,default=USER"
    status="VARNAME"
    lifetime="LT,default=from_type"              // seconds
    />

<counter:inc
    *name="NAME"
    scope="USER|SERVICE|OPERATOR|PROVIDER,default=USER"
    inc="INT64,default=1"        // ignored for some types
    weight="INT,default=1"         // ignored for some types
    status="VARNAME"
    />

<counter:reset
    *name="NAME"
    scope="USER|SERVICE|OPERATOR|PROVIDER,default=USER"
    status="VARNAME"
    />

<counter:get
    *name="NAME"
    *value="VARNAME"
    scope="SYSTEM|USER|SERVICE|OPERATOR|PROVIDER,default=USER"
    function="VAL|AVG|MIN|MAX|SIGMA|other,default=VAL"
    status="VARNAME"
    />

// =============================================

The values of status:
0 -- ok
1 -- not found
2 -- type mismatch
3 -- function not found


The type template TEMPLID contains the following fields:
 type="acc|time|avg|hist"
 param1="..."
 param2="..."
 notification="10"         // seconds


Counter       Arguments
Accumulator   ---
Average       time
TimeSnapshot  time    bins

// ======================================================
The system counters:

# NAME                       TYPE
sys.traffic.global.smpp      timesnapshot    1/10s
sys.traffic.smpp.sme.NAME    timesnapshot    1/5s
sys.traffic.smpp.smsc.NAME   timesnapshot    1/5s
sys.smpp.queue.global        accumulator
sys.smpp.queue.in.NAME       accumulator
sys.smpp.queue.out.NAME      accumulator

session.              
transport.http.
transport.smpp.
